Project Summary:

We’re building a system where IoT devices send real-time data (e.g., temperature, humidity) to a backend via MQTT or HTTP, triggering IBM Cloud Functions. 
These functions process the data and store it in a MongoDB database. The frontend (React) shows real-time updates using WebSockets.

Project Overview:

IoT Device ──▶ IBM Cloud Function ──▶ MongoDB Atlas
                       │
                       └──▶ Notify MERN App (via WebSocket / REST API)
